						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Vīrarājēndra Year 5: 1068 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Beings with the <hi rend="italic">meykīrti</hi> of the king, <hi rend="italic">Vīramē tuṇaiyāgavum.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the construction of stone temple for the god, Paḍampakka-nāyaka dēvar by an official, Maṇakkuḍaiyān Paśuvati Araṅgaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Rājēndra Mūvēndavēḷār (a native) of Maṇkkuḍi in Iḍaiyaṉi-nāḍu (a sub-division) of Vijayarājēndra-vaḷanāḍu in Chōḻa-maṇḍalam. </p>						

